[thinking] **Implementing serialization logic**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering using standard public serialization extension APIs instead of reflection, which sounds like a good approach. I need to implement a subclass of ObjectOutputStream and override the replaceObject method for byte[]—perhaps focusing solely on the BCLMSPrivateKey encoding. Additionally, ObjectInputStream will need a way to resolve EncodedPrivateKey to byte[]. I think a wrapper class in the test can work, but I’m pondering whether a dedicated test file could also include a nested static class.
